    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.58.2" />

                
                <fw type="curatorial">2</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                5835 Vine Street
                Lincoln, Nebraska 68505
                May 1, 1969
                    </dateline>
                   
                   <address>
                <addrLine>Mr. J. Golden Taylor, Editor</addrLine>
                <addrLine><hi rend="underline">Western American Literature</hi></addrLine>
                <addrLine>Colorado State University</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Fort Collins, Colorado 80521</addrLine>
                   </address>
                    
                <salute>Dear Mr. Taylor:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>You have made me unhappy, although with the best intentions.I should like very much to know <hi rend="underline">The Blue God</hi> and review it, but I really should not undertake it now. During the past fall and winter I have had two cataract operations, and cannot take on any considerable amount of reading. Also within the next week I will have the complete manuscript of my biography, and this will require all my attention for some time. If I have any time left over, I feel obliged to continue work on my autobiography.</p>
                
                <p>Really, I am very sorry that I must refuse.</p>
                
                <p>I know your magazine and have high regards for it. Truly your English Department has reason to be proud of it.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With all kind thoughts,</salute>
                
                    <note>JGN:fmb </note>                           <signed>John G. Neihardt</signed>                                               
                </closer>
                
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
